cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the architecture and implementation of the IoT cloud, which involves networking and internet technologies. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - Cloud computing techniques are essential for the successful deployment and management of IoT applications, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The IoT cloud collects and analyzes data, which requires efficient data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the implementation details of the IoT cloud and the services it offers, which involves software engineering techniques. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The IoT cloud involves the control and management of various components and systems, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
